In a press briefing, White House Press Secretary Josh Earnest addressed a range of topics including the unrest in Charlotte, the Syrian conflict, the 9/11 Saudi bill, and the release of hacked information. Earnest emphasized the need to strengthen the relationship between local law enforcement and communities, discussed the investigation into the unintentional strike on Syrian government forces, and expressed concern over the cyber breach of personal information. He also defended the President's decisions on Syria and the Iran deal, and discussed the impact of advanced technology on the workforce. Earnest declined to comment on specific legislation or leaked information.